In a small bowl, sprinkle salt over halved cherry tomatoes; set aside. In another small bowl, mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, and Worcestershire sauce; set aside. Place bacon in a large, deep skillet. Cook over medium-high heat until evenly brown. Drain, crumble, and set aside. In a large bowl, combine chicken, crumbled bacon, cherry tomatoes, celery, parsley, and green onions. Stir in mayonnaise mixture. Chill for 10 minutes before serving.